270 g Chicken Thighs
¾ cup Jasmine Rice
170 g Coleslaw Cabbage Mix
1 unit(s) Mini Cucumber
1 unit(s) Green Onion
4 tbsp Soy Sauce Mirin Blend
2 tbsp Ginger-Garlic Puree
1 tbsp Brown Sugar
1 tbsp Sesame Oil
1 tbsp Seasoned Rice Vinegar
¼ tsp Sugar*
1.5 tbsp Oil*
¼ tsp Salt*
0.13 tsp Pepper*

Before starting, wash and dry all produce.
To a medium pot, add 1 1/4 cups (2 1/2 cups) water and 1/8 tsp (1/4 tsp) salt. Cover and bring to a boil over high.
Using a strainer, rinse rice until water runs clear.
To the boiling water, stir in rice, then reduce heat to low. Cover and cook for 13-15 min, until rice is tender and water is absorbed.
Remove from heat. Set aside, still covered.

Meanwhile, halve cucumber lengthwise. Cut into 1/4-inch half-moons.
Thinly slice green onion.
In a medium bowl, whisk together vinegar, half the sesame oil, 1/4 tsp (1/2 tsp) sugar and 1/2 tbsp (1 tbsp) oil. Season with salt and pepper. (NOTE: This is your coleslaw dressing.)

Pat chicken dry with paper towels. Season with salt and pepper.
Heat a large non-stick pan over medium.
While the pan heats, in a small bowl, combine soy sauce mirin blend, brown sugar, ginger-garlic puree and remaining sesame oil. (NOTE: This is your bulgogi sauce.)
When the pan is hot, add 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) oil, then chicken. Cook for 5-6 min per side, until golden.**

Reduce heat to medium-low.
Add bulgogi sauce (from step 3). Cook for 1-2 min, stirring occasionally, until sauce thickens and coats chicken.

To the bowl with coleslaw dressing (from step 2), add coleslaw cabbage mix and cucumbers.
Fluff rice with a fork. Stir in half the green onions.
Divide rice and coleslaw between bowls. Top rice with chicken.
Spoon sauce over chicken, then sprinkle with remaining green onions.